# AIRO — AI Resume Optimizer
# Environment Variables Configuration
# See RENDER_DEPLOYMENT.md for complete production deployment guide

## Local Development Setup

1. Copy backend variables to `backend/.env`
2. Copy frontend variables to `frontend/.env.local`
3. Run `docker-compose up`

## Backend Environment Variables (`backend/.env`)

```env
# MongoDB Connection
# For development: use local MongoDB or Atlas free cluster
# For production: use MongoDB Atlas connection string
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<user>:<password>@cluster0.mongodb.net/airo_db?retryWrites=true&w=majority
DB_NAME=airo_db

# Security
# Generate with: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
JWT_SECRET_KEY=generate-a-long-random-string-here
JWT_ALGO=HS256

# AI / LLM (Groq) - Get from https://console.groq.com
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...

# External APIs (Optional)
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...         # Required for contribution heatmap

# Email Service (Gmail with App Password)
# Get App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
MAIL_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=your-app-specific-password
MAIL_FROM=noreply@airo.com
MAIL_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_FROM_NAME=AIRO Support

# Frontend URL (for CORS in production)
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

## Frontend Environment Variables (`frontend/.env.local`)

```env
# Backend API URL
# For development: http://localhost:8000
# For production: https://airo-backend-xxx.onrender.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=development

# Memory optimization
NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=1024
```

## Docker Compose Setup

```bash
# Build services
docker-compose build

# Run services
docker-compose up

# Access:
# Frontend: http://localhost:3000
# Backend: http://localhost:5000
# Database: MongoDB (configured in MONGO_URI)
```

## Production Deployment

⚠️ **For Render deployment, see [RENDER_DEPLOYMENT.md](./RENDER_DEPLOYMENT.md)**

Key differences for production:
- Use MongoDB Atlas (not local)
- Set environment variables in Render Dashboard (not .env files)
- Use HTTPS URLs (not http://)
- Enable proper CORS with frontend URL
- Use secure API keys from respective services

